# Testing Standards

## Frameworks by Layer

| Package | Framework | Config |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| `apps/web` | Vitest + @testing-library/react | `vitest.config.ts`, 80% coverage threshold |
| `apps/api` | Jest + Supertest | `jest.config.*` |
| `packages/contracts` | Mocha + Chai (Hardhat) | `hardhat.config.ts` |
| `packages/domain` | Vitest | `vitest.config.ts` |
| `packages/api-client` | Vitest | `vitest.config.ts` |

## Run Commands

```bash
npm run test                              # All workspaces
npm run test -w @nodestay/web             # Frontend only
npm run test -w @nodestay/api             # Backend only
npm run test -w @nodestay/contracts       # Contracts only
npm run test:coverage                     # Global coverage
npm run coverage -w @nodestay/contracts   # Contract coverage (solidity-coverage)
```

## Conventions

- Test files are co-located with source files or in a `test/` subdirectory
- Contract tests use Hardhat's `loadFixture` pattern to reuse deployment state
- API tests use `@nestjs/testing`'s `Test.createTestingModule`
- Mock ERC-20 via `MockERC20.sol` or `MockERC20Config.sol`
- Frontend component tests use `@testing-library/react`'s `render` + `screen`
